  <static seed="1607" source="Contrib/PCC/BasicAlgebra/RationalEquations/solveRationalEquations66.pg">
    <statement><p>Solve the equation.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{ {-\frac{8}{t-8}+8\frac{t}{t+5}}={-\frac{2}{t^{2}-3t-40}}  }</m></p>
<p><fillin characters="31" name="AnSwEr0001"/></p>
</statement>
    <answer>
      <p>
        <m>\left\{\frac{19}{2},\frac{-1}{2}\right\}</m>
      </p>
    </answer>
    <solution><p>To clear fractions in an equation, multiply each side of the equation by a common denominator. For this problem, a common denominator is <m>{\left(t-8\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+5\right)}</m>.</p>
<p><m>\displaystyle{\begin{aligned}
  \amp {-\frac{8}{t-8}+8\frac{t}{t+5}} = {-\frac{2}{t^{2}-3t-40}} \\
  \amp {-\frac{8}{t-8}+8\frac{t}{t+5}} = {-\frac{2}{\left(t-8\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+5\right)}} \\
  \amp {-\frac{8}{t-8}\mathopen{}\left(t-8\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+5\right)+8\frac{t}{t+5}\mathopen{}\left(t-8\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+5\right)} = {-\frac{2}{\left(t-8\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+5\right)}\mathopen{}\left(t-8\right)\mathopen{}\left(t+5\right)} \\
  \amp {-8\mathopen{}\left(t+5\right)+8t\mathopen{}\left(t-8\right)} = -2 \\
  \amp {-8t-40+8t^{2}-64t} = -2 \\
  \amp {8t^{2}-72t-40} = -2 \\
  \amp {8t^{2}-72t-38} = 0 \\
  \amp {2\mathopen{}\left(4t^{2}-36t-19\right)} = 0 \\
  \amp ({2t+1})({2t-19}) = 0 \\
   \amp {2t+1}=0 \:\: or\:\: {2t-19}=0 \\
   \amp t={-{\frac{1}{2}}} \:\: or\:\: t={{\frac{19}{2}}}
\end{aligned}
    }</m></p>
<p>We must check solutions when we solve rational equations. In the original equation, both denominators cannot be <m>0</m>. We set them to <m>0</m>, so we can find out what values to exclude from the solution set.</p>
<p>For this example, it<rsq/>s easy to see we must exclude <m>8</m> and <m>-5</m> from the solution set. There is no conflict with those two solutions we got, so the final solution is <m>t={-{\frac{1}{2}}}</m> and <m>t={{\frac{19}{2}}}</m>.</p>
</solution>
